title: At Least 40 Dead In Russian Strike On Dnipro As Zelenskyy Pursues Ceasefire Talks In Paris | 10 News
description: At least 40 people have been killed and 22 injured in a Russian strike on the Ukrainian city of Dnipro, as rescue crews continue searching the rubble of a five-storey residential building that caught fire.  Officials say civilian infrastructure across the area was heavily damaged, with emergency teams still working through the night.  The attack came as President Volodymyr Zelenskyy arrived at the Élysée Palace for talks with French President Emmanuel Macron - part of a renewed diplomatic push toward potential ceasefire terms.  His Paris visit followed a meeting in Florida between Ukrainian and US officials, which Secretary of State Marco Rubio described as “productive” as both sides revised a Washington-drafted proposal criticised for favouring Russian demands. title: 1K+ Dead: Floods In Sri Lanka, Indonesia, Thailand, Malaysia | 10 News
description: Rescuers in Sri Lanka have been scrambling to deliver aid to more than half a million people hit by Cyclone Ditwah, as the death toll climbs to more than 350.  The cyclone brought the nation's worst floods in a decade when it struck on Friday, triggering landslides.  Widespread flooding has also swept countries in the Southeast Asian region, with more than 600 dead in Indonesia and over 170 killed in Thailand. Three have also been killed in Malaysia.  In Indonesia, thousands of people are reportedly isolated without vital supplies. The country's Minister of Home Affairs Tito Karnavian says the country was ‘not prepared’ for the fallout. title: US President Donald Trump’s MRI Test Results Released By The White House | 10 News
description: The White House physician has revealed US President Donald Trump "remains in excellent overall health" after undergoing a preventative MRI.  White House press secretary Karoline Leavitt read a statement from Captain Sean Barbabella during the briefing on Monday, which stated that the 79-year-old’s physical exam included “advanced imaging” that is "standard for an executive physical" in Trump’s age group.  The release comes as Democrats, including Minnesota Governor Tim Walz, have been pushing for the results of the scan amid concerns about Trump's age in his second term. title: Why Climate Change Could Make Your Coffee More Bitter | 10 News
description: It’s a staple in many of our morning routines, but thanks to climate change your cup of coffee could become more bitter, whether you like it or not.  Almost a third of the world’s coffee beans come from Brazil, with the South American country exporting 2.8 million tonnes of the crop last year.  10’s Late News explains. title: How A Plague In Greece Could Cause A Feta Cheese Shortage | 10 News
description: The world could be facing a shortage of feta cheese as Greece battles a sheep and goat plague.  Hundreds of thousands of animals are being culled after contracting or being exposed to sheep pox, a viral infection that has been spreading across the country for over a year.
